method.description: The HTTP method to use to send the request. If not specified, defaults to GET.

value.title: Value
value.description: The parameter value, this may be a static value, or additionally contain a parameter replacement, e.g. {inputEncoding}. For the partner code parameter, this field should be {partnerCode}.

experimentConfig.title: Experiment Configuration
experimentConfig.description: The value for the parameter will be derived from the equivalent experiment configuration value. If not experiment is present, this parameter will not be included in the final url.

searchAccessPoint.title: Search Access Point

newtab.title: Name
newtab.description: The value for the parameter when searched from the new tab page.

homepage.title: Name
homepage.description: The value for the parameter when searched from the homepage.

searchbar.title: Name
searchbar.description: The value for the parameter when searched from the search bar.

addressbar.title: Name
addressbar.description: The value for the parameter when searched from the address bar.

contextmenu.title: Name
contextmenu.description: The value for the parameter when searched from the context menu.

searchAccessPoint.description: A parameter whose value depends on the access point where the search was initiated.

searchTermParamName.title: Search Term Parameter Name
searchTermParamName.description: The name of the query parameter for the search term. Automatically appended to the end of the query. This may be skipped if `{searchTerm}` is included in the base.

urls.title: URLs

search.title: Search URL
search.description: The URL to use for searches

trending.title: Trending Suggestions URL
trending.description: The URL to use for tending suggestions

suggestions.title: Suggestions URL
suggestions.description: The URL to use for suggestions

urls.description: The URLs associated with the search engine.

recordType.title: Record Type
recordType.description: The type of details that this record contains.

environment.title: Environment

locales.title: Locales
locales.description: An array of locales that this section applies to. 'default' will apply to situations where we have not been able to detect the user's locale.

regions.title: Regions
regions.description: An array of regions that this section applies to. 'default' will apply to situations where we have not been able to detect the user's region.

channels.title: Release Channels
channels.description: An array of release channels that this section applies to (not set = everywhere).

deviceType.title: Device Type
deviceType.description: The device type(s) this section applies to. On desktop when this property is specified and non-empty, the associated section will be ignored.

experiment.title: Experiment
experiment.description: The experiment that this section applies to.

maxVersion.title: Maximum Version
maxVersion.description: The maximum application version this section applies to (less-than comparison).

minVersion.title: Minimum Version
minVersion.description: The minimum application version this section applies to.

applications.title: Application Identifiers
applications.description: The application(s) this section applies to (default/not specified is everywhere). `firefox` relates to Firefox Desktop.

distributions.title: Distributions
distributions.description: An array of distribution identifiers that this applies to.

excludedLocales.title: Excluded Locales
excludedLocales.description: An array of locales that this section should be excluded from. 'default' will apply to situations where we have not been able to detect the user's locale.

excludedRegions.title: Excluded Regions
excludedRegions.description: An array of regions that this section should be excluded from. 'default' will apply to situations where we have not been able to detect the user's region.

allRegionsAndLocales.title: All Regions and Locales
allRegionsAndLocales.description: Indicates that this section applies to all regions and locales. May be modified by excludedRegions/excludedLocales.

excludedDistributions.title: Excluded Distributions
excludedDistributions.description: An array of distribution identifiers that this does not apply to.

environment.description: Specifies details of possible user environments that the engine or variant applies to

partnerCode.title: Partner Code
partnerCode.description: The partner code for the engine or variant. This will be inserted into parameters which include '{partnerCode}'

schema.description: This schema contains the details to build application provided search engines shipped in some Mozilla products. The associated remote settings collection is search-config-v2. Note: the top-level properties section is only required to satisfy remoteSettings. The allOf section provides the full details of the different record types.
